Hello all,
I want to merge two meshes into one mesh and found that the CombineGenerator cannot meet this command. In libMesh a function called stitch_meshes may be of use. However, there exist some errors for me to use this function. Part of my code is as follows:
// Here is a example
LibMeshInit init (argc, argv);
Mesh mesh_org(init.comm());
MeshTools::Generation::build_cube(mesh_org, 5,5,5,0,1,0,1,0,1,HEX8);
auto mesh2 = mesh_org.clone();
MeshTools::Modification::translate(*mesh2, 1, 0, 0);

auto mesh3 = mesh_org.clone();
MeshTools::Modification::translate(*mesh3, 2, 0, 0);

mesh2.stitch_meshes(*mesh3, 2, 4, TOLERANCE, true, true, false, false);
// Here is the error message

error: ‘__gnu_cxx::__alloc_traits<std::allocator<std::unique_ptr<libMesh::MeshBase> >, std::unique_ptr<libMesh::MeshBase> >::value_type’ {aka ‘class std::unique_ptr<libMesh::MeshBase>’} has no member named ‘stitch_meshes’

I would like to know how to correct or avoid this error. Any suggestions would be greatly appreciated.

