Anyhow you have the same problem with the pointer as before
  mesh2.stitch_meshes(*mesh3, 2, 4, TOLERANCE, true, true, false, false);
is not OK. mesh2 is a unique_ptr, so you can do this, you have to do:
  mesh2->stitch_meshes(*mesh3, 2, 4, TOLERANCE, true, true, false, false);

The return value of the function clone() is std::unique_ptr< MeshBase >. And it has no member function called stitched_meshes. So I think the type of mesh_org does not affect the type of mesh2.
